<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Wins 21st NCAA National Championship, Sets NCAA Championship Record</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/rifle-west-virginia-wins-21st-ncaa-national-championship-sets-ncaa-championship-record</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><br /><br />COLUMBUS, Ohio – For the 21st time in program history, the West Virginia University rifle team won the NCAA Rifle National Championship after two days of competition inside the Covelli Center in Columbus on Saturday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg"><media:title>2026 Rifle NCAA National Champions</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/DSC02615.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58864</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Host NCAA Tournament First and Second Rounds</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="we're hosting 1920x1080" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University women's basketball team is set to host the First and Second Rounds of the 2026 NCAA Women's Basketball Tournament, as announced by the NCAA on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png"><media:title>we're hosting 1920x1080</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58863</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Big 12 Opener to Baylor</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/baseball-mountaineers-drop-big-12-opener-to-baylor</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brock Wills" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – The West Virginia University baseball team dropped its Big 12 opener, 7-6, Friday evening at Baylor. The Mountaineers fall to 11-4 overall while the Bears improve to 11-6.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg"><media:title>Brock Wills</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/ENX08870.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:22:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58862</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Scores Fourth Straight 195.0+ Score at No. 21 NC State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/gymnastics-west-virginia-scores-fourth-straight-195-0-score-at-no-21-nc-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/gymnastics-west-virginia-scores-fourth-straight-195-0-score-at-no-21-nc-state</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="sophia rice" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" /><br /><br />RALEIGH, N.C. – The West Virginia University gymnastics team scored a 195.725 to finish in second place behind No. 21 NC State, who scored a 196.65, inside Valvano Arena in Raleigh, North Carolina, on Friday night.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg"><media:title>sophia rice</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/GB703095.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 22:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58861</s:story_id></item><item><title>Naukot Finishes Seventh in 5,000 Meters at NCAA Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/track-field-naukot-finishes-seventh-in-5-000-meters-at-ncaa-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/track-field-naukot-finishes-seventh-in-5-000-meters-at-ncaa-championships</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Joy Naukot" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University sophomore Joy Naukot earned First Team All-America honors after finishing seventh in the women's 5,000 meters at the NCAA Indoor Track and Field Championships on Friday evening in Fayetteville, Ark.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png"><media:title>Joy Naukot</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/5/joynaukot.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 21:04:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58860</s:story_id></item><item><title>Day One Complete at the Schenkel Invitational</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/golf-day-one-complete-at-the-schenkel-invitational</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/golf-day-one-complete-at-the-schenkel-invitational</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="WV shot" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/10/26/WVB09740_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University golf team completed play on Friday after 18 holes of golf at the Schenkel Invitational in Statesboro, Georgia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/26/WVB09740_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/26/WVB09740_large.jpg"><media:title>WV shot</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/26/WVB09740_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 18:07:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58859</s:story_id></item><item><title>Lake Hits Podium, WVU in Fourth After Smallbore at NCAA Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/rifle-lake-hits-podium-wvu-in-fourth-after-smallbore-at-ncaa-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/13/rifle-lake-hits-podium-wvu-in-fourth-after-smallbore-at-ncaa-championship</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Griffin Lake" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/13/DSC07987.jpg" /><br /><br />COLUMBUS, Ohio – Led by junior Griffin Lake's third-place finish in the smallbore competition, the West Virginia University rifle team sits in fourth place after the opening day of the 2026 NCAA Rifle Championships, hosted by Ohio State inside the Covelli Center in Columbus.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/DSC07987.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/DSC07987.jpg"><media:title>Griffin Lake</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/13/DSC07987.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 13 Mar 2026 15:44:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58858</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Road Match at No. 42 Utah</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/tennis-mountaineers-drop-road-match-at-no-42-utah</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/tennis-mountaineers-drop-road-match-at-no-42-utah</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Audrey Moutama" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/12/GB708179.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (6-6, 0-5 Big 12) dropped a 4-0 decision to No. 42 Utah (9-5, 2-2 Big 12) on Thursday afternoon in Salt Lake City.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/GB708179.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/GB708179.jpg"><media:title>Audrey Moutama</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/GB708179.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 20:54:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>15</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58857</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rodriguez Makes Staff Announcements</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/football-rodriguez-makes-staff-announcements</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/football-rodriguez-makes-staff-announcements</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="staff-announcements-2026" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/12/IMG_6187.JPG" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University football coach Rich Rodriguez has announced the promotion of Andrew Warwick to linebackers coach, Garrett Hirsch to assistant general manager and the addition of Paul Padalino to the football staff as a defensive analyst.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/IMG_6187.JPG" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/IMG_6187.JPG"><media:title>staff-announcements-2026</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/IMG_6187.JPG" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 16:52:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58856</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Head to Baylor to Open Big 12 Play</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/baseball-mountaineers-head-to-baylor-to-open-big-12-play</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/baseball-mountaineers-head-to-baylor-to-open-big-12-play</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="MatchupVsBaylor" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/12/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Baylor.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team hits the road to open Big 12 play, March 13-15, against Baylor. First pitch from Magnolia Field at Baylor Ballpark on Friday is set for 7:30 p.m. ET, Saturday for 3 p.m. ET, and Sunday for 12 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Baylor.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Baylor.jpg"><media:title>MatchupVsBaylor</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_Baylor.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 16:01:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58855</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>